{
  "texts": [
    "For conventional seismological analysis, they will enable the reproducible generation of catch-all (near-comprehensive) event catalogues for cryoseismology and facilitate further manual analysis.",
    "They will also enable progress in the wider fields of environmental and geotechnical applications of seismology.",
    "Significantly a semi-automated approach to data analysis is enabled such that machine learning and other automated analyses may be used to enhance pattern detection and dataset exploration.",
    "Improving analysis capabilities, whether by conventional or semi-automated means, should prove to be a valuable step forward in analyzing the response of remote glaciers to global change.",
    "The Cryosphere, 18, 2061-2079, 2024 https://doi.org/10.5194/tc-18-2061-2024 R. B. Latto et al."
  ]
}